Sec. 167.081. DESIGNATION OF FACILITY TO HANDLE CERTIFIED
LIVESTOCK. (a) The commission may designate a stockyard that is in
the tick eradication area or in the free area and is open to the
public for yarding, marketing, and selling livestock as a facility to
handle intrastate movements of livestock certified by an inspector to
be free from ticks or exposure to ticks. A stockyard so designated
shall provide tick-free facilities for the handling of that livestock
in accordance with this subchapter.
(b) A designation under this section is effective for 24 months
following the day on which notice is served, and the commission may
Statute text rendered on: 8/6/2022

